The paper deals with the analysis of basketball data using tensor decomposition, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and data mining. The paper also mentions the use of contextual meta-data, which suggests a focus on data analysis and modeling rather than data collection or visualization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the analysis of social and information networks using machine learning and data mining techniques. Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.DB (Databases).
